# Typography Update Walkthrough

I have updated the application's typography to create a more elegant and professional feel by mixing **Lora** (Serif) and **Inter** (Sans-serif). Both fonts have full support for Vietnamese Unicode.

## Changes Made

### 1. Font Integration
- **Lora (Serif)**: Imported and configured in [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/layout.tsx). It is now the primary font for all headings (`h1` through `h6`) and elements with the `.font-serif` class.
- **Inter (Sans-serif)**: Maintained as the primary body font for maximum readability in data-heavy views.

### 2. Styling Enhancements
- Updated [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/globals.css) to:
  - Define `--font-serif` using the Lora variable.
  - Apply the serif font to headings with a slight letter-spacing refinement (`-0.01em`) and semi-bold weight (`600`).
  - Ensure body text remains clean and legible with Inter.

